# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Arentim — environment template.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. NEVER commit `.env`.
#
# Only VITE_-prefixed vars are exposed to the browser bundle. NEVER prefix a
# secret with VITE_. The Supabase anon key is designed to be public; the
# service_role key, API-Football key, and Gemini key are SECRETS and must live
# ONLY in Supabase Edge Function secrets — never here, never in the client.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Frontend (safe to expose) ---
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SERVER-SIDE SECRETS — do NOT put these in this file or any VITE_ var.
# Set them with the Supabase CLI instead:
#
#   supabase secrets set SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=...
#   supabase secrets set API_FOOTBALL_KEY=...
#   supabase secrets set GEMINI_API_KEY=...
#
# Listed here only as documentation of what the Edge Functions expect:
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY   — full-access key, Edge Functions only
#   API_FOOTBALL_KEY            — dashboard.api-football.com (free tier)
#   GEMINI_API_KEY              — aistudio.google.com/apikey (Flash, free tier)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
